REQUIREMENTS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Supported Systems
-----------------

We have successfully compiled and tested NEXTENS on the following
systems: 

- Linux i386 (2.4): 
  Slackware 8.1 with gcc-2.95.3, 
  RedHat 8.0 with gcc 3.2

- MS Windows (98,2000,XP) under Cygwin (1.3.19) with gcc-3.2.3

It will probably compile on other Unix platforms and with other
versions of gcc well. The sources are *not* compatible with Visual C++
or other native Windiows compilers, because additional software is
used (e.g. Timbl and Mbt) which will not compile with VC++.


Dependencies
------------

Before trying to compile the NEXTENS sources, make sure that you have:

- Succesfully build and installed sources of the Festival Speech
  Synthesis System (version 2.4.2 or 2.4.3) and the Edinburgh Speech
  Tools (version 1.2.1 or 1.2.3).
  See http://www.cstr.ed.ac.uk/projects/festival/


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
BUILD
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Change directory to the one that contains the 'festival' and
   'speech_tools' directories

2. Unpack the Nextens sources with 'tar xvzf nextens-src-1.0-beta.tar.gz'. 

   Do *not* use Windows zip programs (e.g. WinZip), as they may
   corrupts the file format.

3. Change to the Festival directory

4. If you are using a standard installation of Festival, just replace
   your curent Festival config file with the the Nextens config file,
   using : 'cp config/config.nextens config/config'

   If you are using a *non-standard* installation of Festival, that is,
   if you manually modified the Festival config file, then you have to
   add the following line to it:

       ALSO_INCLUDE += NextensFonpars NextensTimbl NextensMbt

5. If you you want to use the interface to Praat,
   you must also add:

       ALSO_INCLUDE += NextensPraat

       ifdef DISPLAY
         COMPILERLIBS += -L/usr/X11R6/lib -lX11
       endif

   Notice that you may have to modify the path according to the
   appropriate location of your X11 libraries.

5. Type 'make' to build the Nextens extensions 


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CONFIGURATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

- If you want to use Dutch by default, put the following line in the
  file festival/lib/siteinit.scm, or alternatively .festivalrc in your
  home directory:

	(set! voice_default 'voice_net_nl_ib_mbrola)

  If you do not have these initialization files, you can create them.



